</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1148,1242,1745,1768]" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
will key to the alternative of couplet &quot; 
<number box="[414,444,1780,1804]" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" value="13.0">13</number>
&quot; with 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Galileo. In" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo. In" box="[523,911,1780,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hypsioma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbara">
<emphasis box="[523,652,1780,1804]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">H. barbara</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Galileo. In
</taxonomicName>
both species the prothorax is trapezoidal and sides are without lateral sulcus; basal elytral crest not projected, sparsely punctate. 
<taxonomicName box="[1073,1237,1816,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hypsioma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosericea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1073,1237,1816,1840]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">H. albosericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1244,1330,1817,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs in the basal declivity of elytra with silky, whitish pubescence; elytra centrally without band or whitish pubescent macula; and humeri without tubercle. In 
<taxonomicName box="[614,742,1888,1912]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hypsioma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbara">
<emphasis box="[614,742,1888,1912]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="443">H. barbara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the elytra have a wide, oblique white pubescent band, and a conspicuous humeral tubercle.
</paragraph>
